Changes recorded 2026-07-02:
- Added Home Assistant config flow support for pairing through the UI.
- Updated component setup so config entries create the media player entity.
- Added pycryptodome as the explicit provider for the Crypto module.
- Adjusted PySmartCrypto pairing so token creation can run without stdin.
- Updated media player imports for newer Home Assistant media player APIs.
- Replaced pairing sys.exit calls with handled errors so Home Assistant is not stopped.
- Removed secret pairing values from default Home Assistant logs.
- Added ARP-cache MAC detection and an options flow for Wake-on-LAN setup.
- Added read-only diagnostic sensors for configured host, port, and MAC address.
- Restored source list filtering so only TV-reported connected sources are selectable.

Changes recorded 2026-07-03:
- Added SSDP discovery so Home Assistant can offer detected Samsung TVs for setup.
- Removed manual MAC address entry from the UI; MAC is now ARP-detected only.
- Removed manual name entry from the UI; discovered TVs use their UPnP name.
- Deduplicated SSDP discovery by Samsung deviceID when multiple services announce the same TV.
- Updated README for UI-based setup, legacy YAML setup, diagnostics, and AI-assisted maintenance disclosure.
- Released fork version 2026.7.3.
- Raised the tested minimum Home Assistant version to 2026.7.0 and released fork version 2026.7.4.
- Added local icon and logo assets for Home Assistant/HACS display and released fork version 2026.7.5.
- Moved local brand assets into Home Assistant's supported brand/ directory and released fork version 2026.7.6.
- Added @BAERnado as code owner and updated the displayed integration name for fork differentiation.
- Renamed the displayed integration name to SamsungTV Encrypted SSDP and released fork version 2026.7.7.
- Replaced BeautifulSoup XML parsing with stdlib XML parsing for SOAP/SSDP responses and released fork version 2026.7.8.
- Added send_key key chaining through media_player.play_media and released fork version 2026.7.9.
